cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the design of wireless communication systems, specifically 5G systems, and investigates the role of frequency reuse in supporting Ultra-Reliable Ubiquitous-Rate Communication (UR2C). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and signal processing, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The paper also deals with system design and optimization, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and analysis, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
